message: Always use the stove on raw ingredients first. For raw grains, the stove will likely yield a 0-value 'cooked' item; use water on it to get a 20-value 'soaked' item. Once you have individual ingredients all at 20 value (cooked vegetables, cooked proteins, soaked grains), combine two of them. Combining a grain and a protein, or a vegetable and a protein, often yields a 60-value item. Combining two vegetables usually yields 40. Avoid combining already combined dishes, as this tends to create 'overcomplicated' items with significantly reduced or negative values. Submit your highest value item (typically 60) once you achieve it to secure the score.
